{"title":"FA DES ADAPT iPad","guid":"","filepath":"/Users/criaah/Vault/📚 Resources/Mapas-Mentales/Entidades clínicas/General/FA DES ADAPT iPad.smmx","root":{"id":"0","parent":"-1","text":"FA + DES: Terapia Antitrombótica\\N(ADAPT AF-DES, NEJM 2026)","guid":"EPxgfeMras4iJIIvM-jEpA","children":[{"id":"1","parent":"0","text":"Contexto\\NClínico","guid":"CKvVnmThWC41gtAfoqVRfA","children":[{"id":"2","parent":"1","text":"FA → anticoagulación LARGO PLAZO (prevenir ACV + embolia sistémica)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"3","parent":"1","text":"ICP + DES → antiagregación (prevenir trombosis stent)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"4","parent":"1","text":"COMBINACIÓN anticoagulante + antiplaquetario → ↑ riesgo sangrado","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"5","parent":"1","text":"Guías previas\\Nal estudio","guid":"t-9ESo5xGGDLAPY08lyRVA","children":[{"id":"6","parent":"5","text":"Interrupción temprana AAS post-ICP","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"7","parent":"5","text":"Continuar NACO + inhibidor P2Y12 por 6-12 meses","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"8","parent":"5","text":"Pasado 1 año → MONOTERAPIA con NACO","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"9","parent":"5","text":"BRECHA: evidencia limitada en DES 2da/3era generación específicamente","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"10","parent":"0","text":"Ensayo\\NADAPT\\NAF-DES","guid":"iaWpfRAXQzwm8I_WBRcpjw","children":[{"id":"11","parent":"10","text":"Diseño","guid":"","children":[{"id":"12","parent":"11","text":"Multicéntrico, aleatorizado, abierto, NO INFERIORIDAD","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"13","parent":"11","text":"32 centros, Corea del Sur","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"14","parent":"11","text":"Aleatorización 1:1 (ITT)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"15","parent":"11","text":"Margen no inferioridad: 3.0 puntos porcentuales","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"16","parent":"11","text":"Poder estadístico 80%, error tipo I unilateral 2.5%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"17","parent":"11","text":"N = 960 pacientes","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"18","parent":"10","text":"Población","guid":"","children":[{"id":"19","parent":"18","text":"Edad 19-85 años, FA confirmada","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"20","parent":"18","text":"ICP + DES 2da o 3era generación → AL MENOS 1 AÑO antes","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"21","parent":"18","text":"CHA2DS2-VASc ≥ 2","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"22","parent":"18","text":"Exclusiones: edad >85a, válvula mecánica, estenosis mitral mod-severa, TVP, DES 1era gen o stent metálico","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"23","parent":"10","text":"Características\\Nbasales","guid":"xvITQjW-_pw_v4xfSQRsiw","children":[{"id":"24","parent":"23","text":"Edad media 71.1 ± 8.5 años | Mujeres: 21.4%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"25","parent":"23","text":"Mediana tiempo ICP → aleatorización: 32.8 meses","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"26","parent":"23","text":"ICP compleja en procedimiento índice: 25.7%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"27","parent":"23","text":"CHA2DS2-VASc mediana: 4 (RIC 3-5)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"28","parent":"23","text":"HAS-BLED mediana: 3 (RIC 2-3)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"29","parent":"23","text":"SCA como presentación inicial: 64.8%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"30","parent":"23","text":"NACO principal: apixabán ~61%","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"31","parent":"0","text":"Intervenciones","guid":"","children":[{"id":"32","parent":"31","text":"GRUPO A →\\NMONOTERAPIA con NACO","guid":"3JRlwE-x6zc3Xx1l2LgcIw","children":[{"id":"33","parent":"32","text":"Apixabán 5 mg 2 veces/día","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"34","parent":"32","text":"Rivaroxabán 20 mg 1 vez/día","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"35","parent":"31","text":"GRUPO B →\\NTERAPIA\\NCOMBINADA","guid":"dTcJb3VJ3BbKys6PbPtMFw","children":[{"id":"36","parent":"35","text":"Apixabán 5 mg 2 veces/día","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"37","parent":"35","text":"Rivaroxabán 15 mg 1 vez/día (DOSIS REDUCIDA)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"38","parent":"35","text":"+ Clopidogrel 75 mg 1 vez/día","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"39","parent":"31","text":"Elección NACO → a discreción del médico tratante","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"40","parent":"31","text":"Ajuste de dosis según criterios preespecificados","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"41","parent":"0","text":"Endpoint Primario\\N(NACE a 12 meses)","guid":"u4OcRUJXjo61kFOEO2UQZA","children":[{"id":"42","parent":"41","text":"Compuesto de: muerte por cualquier causa + IAM + trombosis stent + ACV + embolia sistémica + sangrado mayor o NMCR","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"43","parent":"41","text":"NACE = Net Adverse Clinical Events","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"44","parent":"0","text":"Resultados Principales\\N(12 meses)","guid":"MswUNuXXE7YYM6ujIjOU4Q","children":[{"id":"45","parent":"44","text":"Endpoint\\Nprimario NACE","guid":"Nw0NZlxNMKh8mKnx7L1aoQ","children":[{"id":"46","parent":"45","text":"Monoterapia: 9.6% vs Combinada: 17.2%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"47","parent":"45","text":"Diferencia absoluta: -7.6 pp (IC 95.2%: -11.9 a -3.3)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"48","parent":"45","text":"HR 0.54 (IC 95.2%: 0.37-0.77)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"49","parent":"45","text":"p<0.001 para NO INFERIORIDAD → y para SUPERIORIDAD","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"50","parent":"44","text":"Sangrado\\Nmayor o\\NNMCR","guid":"5JhOeeozaz8l5DtfAbHDhg","children":[{"id":"51","parent":"50","text":"Monoterapia: 5.2% vs Combinada: 13.2%","guid":"asWD3kwWBQUbk68yp6xrPg","children":[]},{"id":"52","parent":"50","text":"Diferencia: -8.0 pp (IC 95%: -11.6 a -4.4)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"53","parent":"50","text":"HR 0.38 (IC 95%: 0.24-0.60) → REDUCCIÓN 62%","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"54","parent":"44","text":"Sangrado mayor aislado","guid":"","children":[{"id":"55","parent":"54","text":"HR 0.37 (IC 95%: 0.18-0.74) → REDUCCIÓN 63%","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"56","parent":"44","text":"Eventos isquémicos\\N(no estadísticamente\\Ndistintos)","guid":"GK13K1QhuMVRNzzgTo8T-g","children":[{"id":"57","parent":"56","text":"Muerte cualquier causa: HR 0.73 (0.37-1.46)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"58","parent":"56","text":"IAM: HR 0.66 (0.19-2.34)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"59","parent":"56","text":"Trombosis stent: HR 0.99 (0.14-7.02) → SIN DIFERENCIA","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"60","parent":"56","text":"ACV: HR 1.24 (0.33-4.64) → SIN DIFERENCIA","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"61","parent":"56","text":"MACE: HR 0.84 (0.43-1.63)","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"62","parent":"0","text":"Análisis de Subgrupos\\N(beneficio consistente)","guid":"KEOpB1Op6YR9BwSLvZmDgQ","children":[{"id":"63","parent":"62","text":"Edad <75 años → HR 0.67","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"64","parent":"62","text":"Edad ≥75 años → HR 0.41 (MAYOR BENEFICIO en adultos mayores)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"65","parent":"62","text":"Sexo femenino → HR 0.32","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"66","parent":"62","text":"SCA inicial → HR 0.50","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"67","parent":"62","text":"ICP compleja → HR 0.42","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"68","parent":"62","text":"Apixabán → HR 0.56","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"69","parent":"62","text":"Rivaroxabán → HR 0.53","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"70","parent":"62","text":"DES 2da gen → HR 0.59 | DES 3era gen → HR 0.50","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"71","parent":"0","text":"Hallazgo Crítico:\\NInfradosificación","guid":"4eCRfllho2UPogMAMHtvcQ","children":[{"id":"72","parent":"71","text":"Monoterapia: 11.3% con dosis inapropiada","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"73","parent":"71","text":"COMBINADA: 29.0% con dosis inapropiada → TRIPLE infradosificación","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"74","parent":"71","text":"Causa: miedo clínico al sangrado al combinar fármacos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"75","parent":"71","text":"Consecuencia: pérdida de eficacia anticoagulante → riesgo ACV aumentado","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"76","parent":"0","text":"Contexto con\\NEstudios Previos","guid":"FVF9AOW7uiKn3BwR_7oUVA","children":[{"id":"77","parent":"76","text":"AFIRE (Japón, 2019) → monoterapia rivaroxabán superior a rivaroxabán + antiplaquetario","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"78","parent":"76","text":"EPIC-CAD → misma dirección","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"79","parent":"76","text":"ADAPT AF-DES → primer ensayo EXCLUSIVO en DES 2da/3era gen + NACOs (sin aspirina, sin warfarina)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"80","parent":"0","text":"Limitaciones","guid":"","children":[{"id":"81","parent":"80","text":"Diseño abierto (mitigado por adjudicación ciega)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"82","parent":"80","text":"Tasas de eventos menores a las esperadas → poder reducido para superioridad (interpretar con precaución)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"83","parent":"80","text":"Solo apixabán y rivaroxabán evaluados → no extrapolar a otros NACOs","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"84","parent":"80","text":"Población exclusivamente asiática (Corea del Sur) → diferencias farmacocinéticas posibles","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"85","parent":"80","text":"Seguimiento solo 12 meses → análisis hasta 2 años en curso","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"86","parent":"0","text":"Implicancias en\\NAdulto Mayor","guid":"A1O5m1XlB67Bm7PjYuKW-w","children":[{"id":"87","parent":"86","text":"Subgrupo ≥75 años → MAYOR beneficio (HR 0.41) → altamente relevante en geriatría","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"88","parent":"86","text":"HAS-BLED alto en cohorte (mediana 3) → riesgo real de sangrado documentado","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"89","parent":"86","text":"Fragilidad no evaluada explícitamente → brecha para futuras investigaciones","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"90","parent":"86","text":"Polifarmacia geriátrica → cada fármaco adicional ↑ riesgo interacciones y sangrado","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"91","parent":"86","text":"Principio STOPP: evitar antiagregante redundante cuando anticoagulación es suficiente","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"92","parent":"0","text":"Perlas\\NClínicas","guid":"NFmB--rX53S8_mfI6EBzPA","children":[{"id":"93","parent":"92","text":"SUSPENDER clopidogrel a ≥1 año de ICP con DES 2da/3era gen si FA con NACO → evidencia de nivel I","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"94","parent":"92","text":"MONOTERAPIA NACO reduce sangrado mayor en 63% sin costo isquémico","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"95","parent":"92","text":"RIESGO TROMBOSIS STENT: sin diferencia significativa (HR 0.99) → DES modernos no requieren doble antiagregación perpetua","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"96","parent":"92","text":"NO INFRADOSIFICAR el NACO → la combinación genera miedo clínico que lleva a subdosificar","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"97","parent":"92","text":"MAYOR BENEFICIO en ≥75 años → paradoja de la infratratamiento en el grupo que más se beneficia","guid":"atn79Aw9uOsPQZersOz_lQ","children":[]},{"id":"98","parent":"92","text":"CHA2DS2-VASc y HAS-BLED como herramientas en cada visita → no solo al inicio","guid":"2s8n0Mg--G_uQKiPfBVw8Q","children":[]},{"id":"99","parent":"92","text":"NO extrapolar a stents metálicos ni DES 1era generación (excluidos del estudio)","guid":"_qaH1JMJD4Y88vdmjKY2nw","children":[]},{"id":"100","parent":"92","text":"APIXABÁN es el NACO más usado y mejor tolerado en adulto mayor → preferir sobre rivaroxabán si polifarmacia alta","guid":"oBioJxykYfZIvIA2l8JlLA","children":[]}]},{"id":"101","parent":"0","text":"VER\\NTAMBIÉN","guid":"i4-HQzli9UBQMNBU8BTMkA","children":[{"id":"102","parent":"101","text":"→ Farmacología Geriátrica - Prescripción y Riesgos (Farmacología y Prescripción)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"103","parent":"101","text":"→ Cardiogeriatría - Fundamentos SIAC (Revisión Cardiogeriatría)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"104","parent":"0","text":"Referencias","guid":"","children":[{"id":"105","parent":"104","text":"1. Lee S-J, Yu HT, Lee Y-J, et al. Therapy for Atrial Fibrillation in Patients with Drug-Eluting Stents. N Engl J Med. 2026;394:658-68.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"106","parent":"104","text":"2. Yasuda S, Kato T, et al. Antithrombotic therapy for atrial fibrillation with stable coronary disease (AFIRE). N Engl J Med. 2019;381(12):1103-1113.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"107","parent":"104","text":"3. Lopes RD, et al. Antithrombotic Therapy after Acute Coronary Syndrome or PCI in Atrial Fibrillation (AUGUSTUS). N Engl J Med. 2019;380(16):1509-1524.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"108","parent":"104","text":"4. January CT, et al. 2023 ACC/AHA/ACCP/HRS Guideline for the Diagnosis and Management of Atrial Fibrillation. J Am Coll Cardiol. 2024;83(1):109-279.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"109","parent":"104","text":"5. Hindricks G, et al. 2020 ESC Guidelines for the diagnosis and management of atrial fibrillation. Eur Heart J. 2021;42(5):373-498.","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},"node_count":109,"relations":[],"cross_references":[],"specialty":"General","folder":"Entidades clínicas/General","filename":"FA DES ADAPT iPad","id":"map_746","resolved_references":[],"title_raw":"FA DES ADAPT iPad"}